<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-12-11T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-12-11T18:00:00-05:00" n="417" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d417">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Council/12–1145: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the United States Representative in Bulgaria</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Barnes</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-11T18:00:00-05:00">December
                                    11, 1945—6 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>398. For your information it is contemplated that during conversations in
                            Moscow scheduled to begin December 15, we will discuss <pb facs="0421" n="409" xml:id="pg_409"/> with Soviet and Brit representatives
                            solution outstanding differences regarding Bulgarian and Rumanian
                                situations.<note n="42" xml:id="d417fn1">See <ref target="frus1945v02">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>
                                </ref>, index entries on Bulgaria and Rumania under Tripartite
                                Conference of Foreign Ministers.</note>
                        </p>
                        <p>Sent to Sofia and Bucharest.<note n="43" xml:id="d417fn2">To Bucharest as
                                No. 644.</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>